prince played by Olivier.

139
00:08:55,618 --> 00:08:57,529
It was the lightest of comedies.

140
00:09:01,583 --> 00:09:04,040
- You in the union?
- No.

141
00:09:04,210 --> 00:09:05,825
Then you can't have a job on the film.

142
00:09:06,004 --> 00:09:07,540
Well, how do I get into the union?

143
00:09:07,714 --> 00:09:09,250
By getting a job on the film.

144
00:09:09,424 --> 00:09:12,006
It's called a closed shop.

145
00:09:14,054 --> 00:09:15,544
I suppose I might be able
to do something for you.

146
00:09:15,722 --> 00:09:19,465
The union owe me a few favors.
We don't have a third yet.

147
00:09:19,642 --> 00:09:24,306
- A third?
- Third assistant director.

148
00:09:24,481 --> 00:09:27,814
- You do know what the job is?
- Assisting the director?

149
00:09:27,984 --> 00:09:29,975
That's the last thing you do!

150
00:09:30,153 --> 00:09:33,862
third's job is to
do whatever the fuck I tell him.

151
00:09:34,449 --> 00:09:37,316
And what are you waiting for?

152
00:09:41,372 --> 00:09:42,612
Colin!

153
00:09:42,791 --> 00:09:45,282
don't shit
on your own doorstep.

154
00:09:45,460 --> 00:09:46,290
- Got it?
- Got it.

155
00:09:46,461 --> 00:09:50,454
The third always stays nearby.

156
00:09:50,632 --> 00:09:52,748
Not in some bloody palace in London.

157
00:09:52,926 --> 00:09:55,087
Book a room at
The Dog & Duck down the road.

158
00:09:55,261 --> 00:09:57,798
It's a bit rough. You'll get used to it.

159
00:09:57,972 --> 00:10:01,385
Now make yourself useful.
Marilyn needs a bodyguard.

160
00:10:01,559 --> 00:10:03,891
Sort something out.

161
00:10:04,395 --> 00:10:07,432
I'm sure you understand the sensitive
nature of the job, Superintendent.

162
00:10:07,607 --> 00:10:10,019
Something about looking
after a cinema actress?

163
00:10:10,193 --> 00:10:13,026
Well, not just any actress.
Marilyn Monroe.

164
00:10:13,196 --> 00:10:15,482
I never had much time
for the pictures.

165
00:10:15,657 --> 00:10:16,863
Excellent.

166
00:10:17,033 --> 00:10:19,024
For the next four months,

167
00:10:19,202 --> 00:10:22,035
you never leave her side.
Day or night.

168
00:10:22,205 --> 00:10:25,242
Her behavior is reputedly
a little erratic.

169
00:10:25,416 --> 00:10:27,748
- She drinks?
- Amongst other things.

170
00:10:27,919 --> 00:10:30,626
- Pills?
- It would be useful if you could, uh,

171
00:10:30,797 --> 00:10:33,038
keep us informed of
her domestic situation.

172
00:10:33,216 --> 00:10:34,126
You want me to spy on her.

173
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:37,542
Well, the odd early warning
if you know she's going to be late.

174
00:10:37,720 --> 00:10:39,381
That kind of thing.

175
00:10:48,356 --> 00:10:49,562
Hello.

176
00:10:49,732 --> 00:10:52,223
Colin Clark. I booked a room.

177
00:10:52,402 --> 00:10:54,984
Ah, right. Here you are.

178
00:10:55,155 --> 00:10:56,861
Sign this.

179
00:10:58,533 --> 00:11:00,239
What brings you up this way?

180
00:11:00,410 --> 00:11:02,025
I'm working on a film at Pinewood.

181
00:11:02,203 --> 00:11:03,784
Oh. What film is that?

182
00:11:03,955 --> 00:11:07,413
It's called The Sleeping Prince. With
Sir Laurence Olivier and Marilyn Monroe,

183
00:11:07,584 --> 00:11:10,747
so I'll be working with them.

184
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:12,831
Room's three quid a week.
First week in advance.

185
00:11:13,006 --> 00:11:14,621
Number two.

186
00:11:14,799 --> 00:11:19,509
And, uh, hope you don't mind,
you'll be sharing with Grace Kelly.

187
00:11:35,778 --> 00:11:39,942
This'll work fine for Marilyn. Oh, and,
uh, Paula will need the room next door.

188
00:11:40,116 --> 00:11:42,107
- I beg your pardon?
- Sorry, who is Paula?

189
00:11:42,285 --> 00:11:44,867
Strasberg. Marilyn's acting coach.

190
00:11:45,038 --> 00:11:46,528
She's nuts about the Method.

191
00:11:46,706 --> 00:11:48,947
Arthur, we've spoken about this before.

192
00:11:49,125 --> 00:11:52,162
Stanislavski and the Method are
perfectly fine in the rehearsal room,

193
00:11:52,337 --> 00:11:54,453
but they don't belong on a film set.

194
00:11:54,631 --> 00:11:55,916
Time is too tight.

195
00:11:59,302 --> 00:12:01,543
Larry! Some good news.

196
00:12:01,721 --> 00:12:03,962
House committee have decided
Miller isn't a communist after all.

197
00:12:04,140 --> 00:12:05,380
Of course he is.

198
00:12:05,558 --> 00:12:08,641
All those pain in the ass
New York intellectuals are Reds.

199
00:12:08,811 --> 00:12:11,803
Which means she'll be flying
in next week on schedule.

200
00:12:11,981 --> 00:12:14,313
- Excellent news.
- She'll have to be met.

201
00:12:14,484 --> 00:12:16,475
Well, naturally Vivien and I
will be there to greet her,

202
00:12:16,653 --> 00:12:19,065
but let's keep it low key, shall we?

203
00:12:19,239 --> 00:12:21,480
You join us here at London Airport,

204
00:12:21,658 --> 00:12:24,115
where it is absolute mayhem.

205
00:12:32,627 --> 00:12:34,492
Marilyn! This way! Get out of the way!

206
00:12:48,935 --> 00:12:52,348
With her is her new husband,
America's most celebrated playwright

207
00:12:52,522 --> 00:12:55,013
and author of Death of a Salesman,
Arthur Miller.

208
00:12:57,860 --> 00:12:59,851
Beautiful. You're looking at
tomorrow's front page, boys.

209
00:13:00,029 --> 00:13:02,020
- We'll have to get them into the hall.
- Sir Laurence Olivier

210
00:13:02,198 --> 00:13:05,656
and Scarlett O'Hara herself,
Vivien Leigh, are set to greet them.

211
00:13:05,827 --> 00:13:09,285
American acting royalty
meeting British acting royalty.

212
00:13:10,248 --> 00:13:13,035
Gentlemen, it is my especial pleasure

213
00:13:13,209 --> 00:13:17,202
to introduce a woman
who clearly needs no introduction.

214
00:13:17,380 --> 00:13:19,541
Marilyn! How do you like being married?

215
00:13:20,049 --> 00:13:21,880
Well, I like it. I like it a lot.

216
00:13:22,051 --> 00:13:24,383
- Is this third time lucky?
- You bet it is.

217
00:13:24,554 --> 00:13:27,045
Is it true you want to be
a classical actress now?

218
00:13:27,223 --> 00:13:29,134
Well, I want to be
the best actress I can be.

219
00:13:29,309 --> 00:13:32,051
There's a rumor you're going to be in
The Brothers Karamazov, on Broadway.

220
00:13:32,228 --> 00:13:36,187
Ooh.
I'm... considering it.

221
00:13:36,357 --> 00:13:37,563
Which of them will you be playing?

222
00:13:37,734 --> 00:13:39,315
I'll be playing Grushenka.

223
00:13:39,485 --> 00:13:42,477
- Can you spell that?
- Sure. Can you?

224
00:13:44,657 --> 00:13:47,820
Vivien, you created
the role of Elsie on stage.

225
00:13:47,994 --> 00:13:49,905
Have you any advice for Marilyn?

226
00:13:50,079 --> 00:13:52,320
I am sure if Miss Monroe
needs any advice,

227
00:13:52,498 --> 00:13:54,409
she'll get it from her director.

228
00:13:54,584 --> 00:13:57,371
I hear he's terribly good.

229
00:13:57,545 --> 00:13:58,785
Marilyn!

230
00:14:01,090 --> 00:14:03,126
Are you happy with your last film?

231
00:14:03,301 --> 00:14:05,383
Marilyn!

232
00:14:05,553 --> 00:14:08,420
Is it true you wear nothing
in bed except perfume?

233
00:14:08,598 --> 00:14:09,553
Ooh.

234
00:14:09,724 --> 00:14:13,512
Darling, as I'm in England, let's say I
sleep in nothing but Yardley's Lavender.

235
00:14:29,035 --> 00:14:30,320
Smile, Marilyn!

236
00:14:34,624 --> 00:14:36,956
OK, let's get a snap of the newlyweds.

237
00:14:37,126 --> 00:14:39,788
Smile, Arthur. It's not a firing squad.

238
00:14:41,589 --> 00:14:42,795
This is some place you found.

239
00:14:42,965 --> 00:14:45,126
You have my new assistant
Colin to thank for that.

240
00:14:45,301 --> 00:14:48,134
Colin, this is Milton Greene.
You must be very nice to him.

241
00:14:48,304 --> 00:14:50,795
He owns half of
Marilyn Monroe Productions.

242
00:14:50,973 --> 00:14:52,964
- Forty-nine percent, Larry.
- Have a cigarette.

243
