1046
01:08:53,379 --> 01:08:55,995
Oh, my...

1047
01:09:58,152 --> 01:10:00,939
Colin. What are you doing here?

1048
01:10:02,573 --> 01:10:04,609
Uh, I came in through the window.

1049
01:10:04,784 --> 01:10:05,944
Milton thought that you were sick.

1050
01:10:07,453 --> 01:10:09,284
Oh.

1051
01:10:10,039 --> 01:10:12,030
The window.

1052
01:10:12,208 --> 01:10:14,039
How romantic.

1053
01:10:14,210 --> 01:10:16,292
That's just like Romeo and Juliet.

1054
01:10:18,339 --> 01:10:22,048
What... Why would
they say that I'm sick?

1055
01:10:26,597 --> 01:10:28,133
Please.

1056
01:10:29,684 --> 01:10:31,595
Please don't take any more.

1057
01:10:32,895 --> 01:10:36,387
Who's this? Who's that?

1058
01:10:36,566 --> 01:10:40,479
That's my mama.
She bought me a white piano.

1059
01:10:42,280 --> 01:10:45,067
Right before they
took her to the asylum.

1060
01:10:45,241 --> 01:10:47,823
I grew up in other
people's homes, mostly.

1061
01:10:50,413 --> 01:10:52,153
Is that Abraham Lincoln?

1062
01:10:52,331 --> 01:10:54,492
That's my dad.

1063
01:10:54,667 --> 01:10:59,001
Well, I don't know who my real father
is, so it may as well be him, right?

1064
01:11:04,177 --> 01:11:07,840
Do you have a home, Colin?
A real one?

1065
01:11:08,681 --> 01:11:12,515
- With a mama and a daddy?
- Yes, I do.

1066
01:11:12,685 --> 01:11:14,721
Do they love you?

1067
01:11:15,980 --> 01:11:17,561
I'm sure that they do.

1068
01:11:17,732 --> 01:11:21,941
Mm. You're lucky.

1069
01:11:22,945 --> 01:11:24,526
Yes.

1070
01:11:25,948 --> 01:11:28,155
Do you love me, Colin?

1071
01:11:30,161 --> 01:11:31,742
Yes.

1072
01:11:35,291 --> 01:11:38,033
You're like some Greek goddess to me.

1073
