1222
01:24:43,662 --> 01:24:46,495
I was wondering if you were
doing anything on Saturday.

1223
01:24:48,041 --> 01:24:49,827
I'm washing my hair.

1224
01:24:54,590 --> 01:24:55,875
Did she break your heart?

1225
01:24:58,594 --> 01:24:59,709
A little.

1226
01:25:01,179 --> 01:25:03,010
Good. It needed breaking.

1227
01:25:14,484 --> 01:25:16,395
We're back, everyone!

1228
01:25:16,570 --> 01:25:17,730
All right...

1229
01:25:38,884 --> 01:25:43,344
You do look, my son, in a moved
sort, as if you were dismayed.

1230
01:25:43,513 --> 01:25:45,674
Be cheerful, sir.

1231
01:25:47,100 --> 01:25:50,513
Our revels now are ended.

1232
01:25:52,147 --> 01:25:56,140
We are such stuff

1233
01:25:56,318 --> 01:25:59,185
as dreams are made on,

1234
01:25:59,363 --> 01:26:03,231
and our little life

1235
01:26:03,408 --> 01:26:07,697
is rounded with a sleep.

1236
01:26:07,871 --> 01:26:09,577
Prospero.

1237
01:26:14,586 --> 01:26:16,201
She's quite wonderful.

1238
01:26:17,923 --> 01:26:19,834
No training, no craft to speak of.

1239
01:26:20,008 --> 01:26:22,545
No guile, just pure instinct.
She's astonishing.

1240
01:26:22,719 --> 01:26:26,382
- You should tell her that.
- Oh, I will. But she won't believe me.

1241
01:26:26,556 --> 01:26:28,922
President Taft.

1242
01:26:29,101 --> 01:26:31,217
It's probably
what makes her great.

1243
01:26:32,270 --> 01:26:35,512
It's almost certainly what
makes her so profoundly unhappy.

1244
01:26:35,691 --> 01:26:39,400
Oh, Miss Marina,
won't you have some champagne?

1245
01:26:39,569 --> 01:26:42,936
Oh, I don't know, Your Grand Ducal.
You really think I ought?

1246
01:26:43,115 --> 01:26:45,606
I tried my best to change her,

1247
01:26:45,784 --> 01:26:48,901
but she remains brilliant, despite me.

1248
01:26:49,079 --> 01:26:54,244
Maybe just up to... Ah!

1249
01:26:54,793 --> 01:26:56,954
Do you know, I think directing a movie

1250
01:26:57,129 --> 01:26:59,541
has to be just about
the best job ever invented.

1251
01:27:00,549 --> 01:27:02,710
But Marilyn's cured me
of ever wanting to do it again.

1252
01:27:02,884 --> 01:27:05,341
Well, now I'm back to the theater.

1253
01:27:05,512 --> 01:27:07,252
John Osborne's writing a piece for me.

1254
01:27:07,431 --> 01:27:10,673
Sir, I thought you hated
all that Royal Court stuff.

1255
01:27:10,851 --> 01:27:13,809
Well, Miller made me see
things a little differently.

1256
01:27:16,648 --> 01:27:18,138
Thank you, Colin, for all your help.

1257
01:27:26,867 --> 01:27:28,698
Glad you ran away to the circus?

1258
01:27:37,502 --> 01:27:39,788
My dear.

1259
01:27:39,963 --> 01:27:42,420
Uh... ow.

1260
01:27:42,591 --> 01:27:46,083
I've got a solemn word
of warning for you.

1261
01:27:46,261 --> 01:27:47,842
What is that, my beloved?

1262
01:27:49,306 --> 01:27:51,217
You know what's going to happen.

1263
01:27:52,934 --> 01:27:55,425
I'm going to fall in love with you.

1264
01:27:57,689 --> 01:27:59,771
I'm going to fall in love with you

1265
01:27:59,941 --> 01:28:03,058
because I always, always do.

1266
01:28:24,090 --> 01:28:26,547
There you go.

1267
01:28:42,984 --> 01:28:44,940
Buy a girl a drink?

1268
01:28:47,697 --> 01:28:49,688
I'll get another one
of those, please, Barry.

1269
01:28:53,411 --> 01:28:55,743
I wasn't going to leave
without saying goodbye.

1270
01:28:57,624 --> 01:28:59,080
Don't forget me.

1271
01:29:02,254 --> 01:29:03,539
As if I could.

1272
01:29:03,713 --> 01:29:06,580
Everybody else on the picture
wishes they could.

1273
01:29:06,758 --> 01:29:08,669
They don't understand you.

1274
01:29:12,138 --> 01:29:13,878
Walk me to my car?

1275
01:29:17,310 --> 01:29:18,675
Nice place you got here.

1276
01:29:50,468 --> 01:29:52,129
Thanks for being on my side.

1277
01:30:01,855 --> 01:30:04,972
Looking a couple of inches taller
than when I first saw you.

1278
01:30:11,573 --> 01:30:15,236
her embrace.

1279
01:30:16,369 --> 01:30:18,200
Her belief in me.

1280
01:30:18,371 --> 01:30:21,738
And the joy she gave.
That was her gift.

1281
01:30:23,335 --> 01:30:26,953
When I think of her now, I think
of that time when a dream came true.

1282
01:30:27,756 --> 01:30:31,374
And my only talent
was not to close my eyes.

1283
01:30:41,811 --> 01:30:45,554
♪ That old black magic

1284
01:30:45,732 --> 01:30:49,941
♪ Has me in its spell

1285
01:30:50,111 --> 01:30:53,854
♪ That old black magic

1286
01:30:54,032 --> 01:30:58,196
♪ That you weave so well

1287
01:30:58,370 --> 01:31:03,535
♪ And down and down I go

1288
01:31:03,708 --> 01:31:07,792
♪ Round and round I go

1289
01:31:07,963 --> 01:31:09,544
♪ In a spin

1290
01:31:09,714 --> 01:31:13,172
♪ Lovin' that spin I'm in

1291
01:31:13,343 --> 01:31:17,086
♪ Under that old black magic

1292
01:31:17,263 --> 01:31:19,879
♪ Called love

1293
01:31:21,226 --> 01:31:24,059
♪ For you're the lover

1294
01:31:24,229 --> 01:31:27,642
♪ I have waited for

1295
01:31:27,816 --> 01:31:30,273
♪ The mate that fate

1296
01:31:30,443 --> 01:31:34,436
♪ Had me created for

1297
01:31:34,614 --> 01:31:40,405
♪ But every time your lips meet mine

1298
